---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const faq = [
  { q: 'Is Spires Digital only for Shopify brands?', a: 'No. Shopify is a core platform, but the growth framework applies to any ecommerce business with reliable store, customer and channel data.' },
  { q: 'Can we start with one channel?', a: 'Yes. The diagnosis considers the whole journey, but the initial scope can focus on one constraint such as Google Shopping, Meta creative, SEO, CRO or retention.' },
  { q: 'How do you decide which area to prioritise?', a: 'We compare commercial upside, evidence confidence, implementation effort and dependencies. The best first project is often the smallest change that unlocks better decisions or improves every acquisition channel.' },
];
const schema = { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage', mainEntity: faq.map(item => ({ '@type': 'Question', name: item.q, acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: item.a } })) };
---

<BaseLayout title="Ecommerce Growth Agency" description="A connected ecommerce growth system across paid media, SEO, CRO, Shopify, email retention, affiliate and analytics." schema={schema}>
  <div class="breadcrumbs-wrap"><Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Ecommerce growth' }]} /></div>
  <section class="ecom-hero hero-dark"><div class="container hero-grid"><div><span class="badge">Ecommerce growth agency</span><h1>Scale the customer journey, not a collection of channels.</h1><p>More traffic is useful only when the store converts it, the customer returns and the economics support the next pound of investment.</p><div class="page-hero-actions"><a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg btn-arrow">Get an ecommerce growth plan</a><a href="/tools/growth-assessment" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">Find your current constraint</a></div></div><div class="journey-map"><div class="journey-head"><span>Connected growth model</span><span>Commercial view</span></div><div class="journey-stage"><span>01</span><div><strong>Acquire</strong><small>Demand and customer cost</small></div><b>Google · Meta · SEO · Affiliate</b></div><div class="journey-stage"><span>02</span><div><strong>Convert</strong><small>Experience and order value</small></div><b>CRO · Shopify · Merchandising</b></div><div class="journey-stage"><span>03</span><div><strong>Retain</strong><small>Repeat purchase and LTV</small></div><b>Email · Automation · Loyalty</b></div><div class="journey-stage"><span>04</span><div><strong>Measure</strong><small>Margin and decision confidence</small></div><b>GA4 · Attribution · Profit</b></div></div></div></section>

  <section class="section surface"><div class="container"><div class="section-heading"><span class="eyebrow">Built for the real operating questions</span><h2>The dashboard says revenue is up. What happened to profit?</h2><p>Ecommerce teams are asked to make investment decisions across platforms that use different attribution, incentives and definitions of success.</p></div><div class="question-grid"><article><span>Acquisition</span><h3>How much can we afford to pay for a new customer?</h3><a href="/tools/ecommerce-profit-calculator">Model break-even CAC →</a></article><article><span>Conversion</span><h3>Why do qualified visitors leave without buying?</h3><a href="/services/cro-shopify">Find conversion friction →</a></article><article><span>Retention</span><h3>How do we reduce dependency on the next paid click?</h3><a href="/services/email-retention">Grow repeat revenue →</a></article><article><span>Measurement</span><h3>Which channel actually created incremental value?</h3><a href="/services/analytics-attribution">Improve decision confidence →</a></article></div></div></section>

  <section class="section model-section"><div class="container"><div class="section-heading center"><span class="eyebrow">The operating model</span><h2>Each growth lever has a job and a shared scorecard.</h2></div><div class="model-table"><div class="model-head"><span>Stage</span><span>Primary question</span><span>Measures that matter</span><span>Services</span></div><div><strong>Acquire</strong><p>Can we reach valuable customers at a sustainable cost?</p><span>CAC · new-customer ROAS · contribution</span><nav><a href="/services/ppc-management">PPC</a><a href="/services/meta-ads">Meta</a><a href="/services/ecommerce-seo">SEO</a><a href="/services/affiliate-management">Affiliate</a></nav></div><div><strong>Convert</strong><p>Can more qualified sessions become profitable orders?</p><span>CVR · AOV · checkout completion</span><nav><a href="/services/cro-shopify">CRO &amp; Shopify</a></nav></div><div><strong>Retain</strong><p>Can the first order become a valuable relationship?</p><span>Repeat rate · time to second order · LTV</span><nav><a href="/services/email-retention">Email &amp; retention</a></nav></div><div><strong>Measure</strong><p>Can the team make the next decision with confidence?</p><span>MER · margin · event quality · incrementality</span><nav><a href="/services/analytics-attribution">Analytics</a></nav></div></div></div></section>

  <section class="section surface"><div class="container split"><div class="split-copy"><span class="eyebrow">How an engagement starts</span><h2>Diagnose before prescribing.</h2><p>The first review considers the complete commercial system, even when the resulting project focuses on one channel.</p><ol class="engagement-steps"><li><span>1</span><div><strong>Economics</strong><p>Margin, AOV, repeat rate, customer targets and budget.</p></div></li><li><span>2</span><div><strong>Journey</strong><p>Demand, merchandising, conversion and lifecycle friction.</p></div></li><li><span>3</span><div><strong>Evidence</strong><p>Tracking quality, current performance and customer signals.</p></div></li><li><span>4</span><div><strong>Roadmap</strong><p>Priorities scored by impact, confidence, effort and dependency.</p></div></li></ol></div><div class="fit-panel"><span>Usually a strong fit for</span><h3>Brands with product-market fit and a growth question that crosses team boundaries.</h3><ul class="check-list"><li>Established stores ready to improve efficiency</li><li>Brands preparing to scale paid acquisition</li><li>Teams planning a Shopify redesign or migration</li><li>Businesses with conflicting channel reports</li><li>Retailers building a second or third acquisition channel</li></ul><a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-arrow">Discuss the growth question</a></div></div></section>

  <section class="section surface-warm"><div class="container"><div class="section-heading"><span class="eyebrow">Start with a useful tool</span><h2>Get an immediate answer from the numbers you already have.</h2></div><div class="tool-links"><a href="/tools/ecommerce-profit-calculator"><span>Most useful first</span><h3>Profit &amp; break-even ROAS calculator</h3><p>Find the ROAS, MER and CAC your actual cost structure can support.</p><strong>Open calculator →</strong></a><a href="/tools/channel-budget-planner"><span>Planning</span><h3>Channel budget planner</h3><p>Work backwards from a revenue target to traffic, orders and acquisition budget.</p><strong>Build a scenario →</strong></a><a href="/tools/growth-assessment"><span>Diagnostic</span><h3>Store growth assessment</h3><p>Identify whether acquire, convert, retain or measure is the likely constraint.</p><strong>Start assessment →</strong></a></div></div></section>

  <section class="section surface"><div class="container-narrow"><div class="section-heading center"><span class="eyebrow">Questions</span><h2>Before you choose a channel.</h2></div><div class="faq-list">{faq.map(item => <details><summary>{item.q}</summary><p>{item.a}</p></details>)}</div></div></section>
  <section class="cta-section"><div class="container"><h2>Find the next move that improves the whole system.</h2><p>Share the context. We will return a commercially prioritised ecommerce growth plan.</p><a href="/contact" class="btn btn-white btn-lg btn-arrow">Request your free review</a></div></section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .ecom-hero{padding-top:5rem}.hero-grid{position:relative;z-index:1;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.05fr .75fr;gap:clamp(3rem,7vw,6rem);align-items:center}.journey-map{padding:1rem;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.15);border-radius:var(--radius);background:rgba(255,255,255,.07)}.journey-head{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;padding:.4rem;color:#aab4c5;font-size:.67rem;font-weight:800}.journey-stage{display:grid;grid-template-columns:auto 1fr auto;gap:.75rem;align-items:center;margin-top:.6rem;padding:.9rem;border-radius:10px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.07)}.journey-stage>span{display:grid;width:30px;height:30px;place-items:center;border-radius:8px;background:rgba(117,230,211,.12);color:#91eadb;font-size:.62rem;font-weight:800}.journey-stage strong,.journey-stage small{display:block}.journey-stage strong{color:white}.journey-stage small{color:#9da8ba;font-size:.62rem}.journey-stage b{color:#cbd2df;font-size:.62rem;font-weight:600}.question-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:1rem}.question-grid article{min-height:250px;padding:1.5rem;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--radius);background:var(--canvas)}.question-grid article>span,.tool-links>a>span{color:var(--violet-dark);font-size:.68rem;font-weight:800;text-transform:uppercase}.question-grid h3{max-width:470px;margin:2.5rem 0 1rem;font-size:clamp(1.4rem,2.6vw,2rem)}.question-grid a,.tool-links strong{color:var(--violet-dark);font-size:.78rem;font-weight:800}.model-section{background:#e9e8ff}.model-table{overflow:hidden;border:1px solid #d0cef7;border-radius:var(--radius);background:#d0cef7}.model-head,.model-table>div:not(.model-head){display:grid;grid-template-columns:.4fr 1.2fr 1fr 1fr;gap:1rem;padding:1rem 1.2rem;background:#f8f7ff}.model-head{background:var(--ink)!important;color:#cbd2df;font-size:.68rem;font-weight:800;text-transform:uppercase}.model-table>div+div{border-top:1px solid #d0cef7}.model-table strong{color:var(--ink)}.model-table p,.model-table>div>span{color:var(--slate);font-size:.8rem}.model-table nav{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:.35rem}.model-table nav a{padding:.3rem .5rem;border-radius:999px;background:var(--violet-soft);color:var(--violet-dark);font-size:.62rem;font-weight:800}.engagement-steps{display:grid;gap:.6rem;margin-top:1.5rem;list-style:none}.engagement-steps li{display:grid;grid-template-columns:auto 1fr;gap:.7rem}.engagement-steps li>span{display:grid;width:30px;height:30px;place-items:center;border-radius:50%;background:var(--ink);color:white;font-size:.62rem}.engagement-steps strong{color:var(--ink)}.engagement-steps p{margin:0;color:var(--slate);font-size:.8rem}.fit-panel{padding:clamp(1.4rem,3vw,2rem);border-radius:var(--radius);background:var(--ink);color:#cbd2df}.fit-panel>span{color:#91eadb;font-size:.68rem;font-weight:800;text-transform:uppercase}.fit-panel h3{margin:1rem 0 1.5rem;color:white;font-size:clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.2rem)}.fit-panel .check-list{margin-bottom:1.5rem;font-size:.82rem}.tool-links{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1rem}.tool-links>a{min-height:290px;padding:1.5rem;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--radius);background:white}.tool-links h3{margin:2.5rem 0 .7rem}.tool-links p{margin-bottom:1rem;color:var(--slate);font-size:.84rem}.faq-list{display:grid;gap:.7rem}.faq-list details{border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--radius-sm);background:white}.faq-list summary{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;padding:1.2rem;cursor:pointer;color:var(--ink);font-weight:750;list-style:none}.faq-list summary::after{content:'+';color:var(--violet-dark)}.faq-list details[open] summary::after{content:'−'}.faq-list p{padding:0 1.2rem 1.2rem;color:var(--slate)}@media(max-width:900px){.hero-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.model-head{display:none}.model-table>div:not(.model-head){grid-template-columns:1fr}.tool-links{grid-template-columns:1fr}}@media(max-width:650px){.question-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.journey-stage{grid-template-columns:auto 1fr}.journey-stage b{grid-column:2}}
</style>
